The busiest time in Kenyan history is during the general elections. Leaders take such opportunities to hack deals which shall benefit them after elections. Living in a society where ethnic diversity is optional shows that citizens elect politicians rather than leaders. The introduction of two bills to amend the constitution is sincerely welcomed. But reducing the number of leaders while we still elect the same characters will not change the situation. What needs to change is the type of leaders we choose to avoid recycling scandalous politicians with a questionable image.  Emuhaya